TY  - JOUR
AU  - Aslan, Hadiye
AU  - Kalimipalli, Madhu
AU  - Kumar, Praveen
AU  - Venugopal, Buvaneshwaran
T1  - Product Market Competition, Mergers and Acquisitions, and Covenant Redesign
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfae019
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
SP  - 880
EP  - 914
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - Industry competition shocks are major drivers of mergers and acquisitions (M&amp;A). We document strong positive effects of competition shocks on M&amp;A-related covenant redesign. Acquiring firms in high-competition environments are significantly more likely to undertake tender offer bond repurchases and reduce restrictions on mergers, investments, payouts, and financing, but increase change-in-control covenants. This effect is stronger for larger, more profitable firms. Moreover, announcement returns from M&amp;A transactions of redesigning firms in more competitive settings are significantly higher, while acquisition deal premiums are lower. Our study shows the significant effect of industry competition shocks on debt recontracting in M&amp;A. (JEL G32, G34)
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfae019
ER  - 




